<TITLE> CID gets 5 days to grill 19 more BDR men </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 16 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court granted CID five days to grill 19 BDR members accused of involvement in the 25-26 Feb. Peelkhana mutiny. Metropolitan magistrate Faisal Atik Bin Quader remanded the 19 into CID custody on petition by investigation officer Abdul Qahhar Akhand. Akhand, a senior assistant superintendent, sought seven days remand, telling the court the accused looted weapons from the BDR armoury and brutally killed army officers deputed to the border force. The IO claimed other accused already had given information on the accused, and further interrogation was needed to gather more information from them. The same court also sent another accused, Al Masum, to jail pending charges after his three-day remand. b
